1
00:00:09,133 --> 00:00:11,345
I drove cross-country in a car like this.
我曾经开着一辆这样的车横越国家.

2
00:00:12,345 --> 00:00:13,216
Did it make it?
那辆车做到了吗?

3
00:00:13,994 --> 00:00:14,680
Eventually.
最后还是做到了.

4
00:00:15,473 --> 00:00:16,362
We started in Boston.
我们从波士顿出发.

5
00:00:17,458 --> 00:00:20,312
Then we went to Ohio to visit some relatives.
然后去俄亥俄(Ohio)拜访了几个亲戚.

6
00:00:21,333 --> 00:00:21,837
Then out west.
然后就一直往西开.

7
00:00:23,062 --> 00:00:23,723
What was that like?
西部是什么样子?

8
00:00:24,688 --> 00:00:27,529
Fantastic. Everything's bigger.
美不胜收. 所有东西都比这里的大.

9
00:00:28,557 --> 00:00:29,373
The mountains are higher.
山更高.

10
00:00:29,917 --> 00:00:30,711
The canyons are deeper.
峡谷更深.

11
00:00:32,713 --> 00:00:34,137
The land goes on and on.
土地无边无际.

12
00:00:35,431 --> 00:00:36,027
Where did you stay?
你们住在哪儿?

13
00:00:37,885 --> 00:00:38,305
We camped.
我们宿营.

14
00:00:39,476 --> 00:00:43,381
Except for one week we stayed with a family in Butte,Montana.
除了有一个星期我们是和一家人住在一起的 在蒙大拿洲(Montana)比尤特市(Butte).

15
00:00:44,265 --> 00:00:45,213
More relatives?
又是亲戚?

16
00:00:46,583 --> 00:00:49,334
No, the car broke down in front of their house.
No, 车在他们的房子前面坏掉了.

17
00:00:51,224 --> 00:00:53,170
You know what else was great about camping?
你知道宿营还有什么别的好处吗?

18
00:00:54,004 --> 00:00:54,344
What?
什么?

19
00:00:54,922 --> 00:00:55,641
It was very quiet.
非常安静.

20
00:00:57,689 --> 00:00:58,205
Yeah,well...
Yeah,well...

21
00:01:02,784 --> 00:01:03,779
Shall we put on some music?
我们要不要来点音乐?

22
00:01:04,511 --> 00:01:04,870
Yes!
Yes!

23
00:01:12,225 --> 00:01:12,700
Much better!
现在好多了!

